@strong{@code{#000027} (Void Navy) is the mandatory background for ALL
Spacecraft Software surfaces.} No alternative background is permitted.
This is non-negotiable.

@strong{Scope of the contrast guarantee.} Every foreground token above is
verified against the Void Navy background and passes WCAG Level AA
(Molten Amber 7.64:1, Steel Blue 4.77:1, Radium Green 14.87:1, Red Oxide
6.74:1, Liquid Coolant 14.74:1). That guarantee covers
@strong{foreground-on-background pairings only}. Palette tokens paired with
@emph{each other} are mostly far below the 3:1 floor --- Molten Amber on
Red Oxide is 1.13:1 and Radium Green on Liquid Coolant is 1.01:1, which is
indistinguishable. Therefore:

@itemize
@item
Rendering palette-colored @strong{text on a palette-colored fill} (a chip,
badge, filled button, or selected row) is @strong{forbidden} unless that
specific pair has been measured at ≥4.5:1 for text, or ≥3:1 for
non-text UI boundaries.
@item
Color may never be the @strong{sole} carrier of meaning. Every colored
status must also carry a text tag or symbol --- see §18.2.
@end itemize

